@section RUN-020
title: Immediate Actions
summary: Stabilize service first, investigate in parallel
links: CMD-ROLLBACK-001
content:
<<<
1) Start on-call bridge
2) Pause risky rollout / rollback decision
3) Check critical dependencies
4) Apply temporary mitigation
>>>

@section RUN-030
title: Communication
summary: Keep updates consistent and time-bound
links: TEMPLATE-INCIDENT
content:
<<<
[Internal updates]
- First update due:
- Update cadence:

[External updates]
- Status-page trigger:
- Customer communication channel:
>>>

@section RUN-040
title: Exit Criteria
summary: Close incident only after metrics normalize and follow-ups are filed
links: CHECKLIST-CLOSE
content:
<<<
[Closure checks]
1) Failure-rate normalized
2) Latency normalized
3) Backlog cleared

[Follow-up]
- Incident-case logged (30_shared/errFix)
- Postmortem scheduled if needed
- Action tickets created
>>>

